node.title: NSW Police expect William Tyrrell search time to 'double' due to wild weather
node.alt: A young boy is smiling in a red t-shirt.
node.description: NSW Police say the search for William Tyrrell's remains on the Mid North Coast "may be extended" due to poor weather forecast to lash the east coast.
node.content:
["NSW Police say the search for William Tyrrell's remains on\u00a0the Mid North Coast\u00a0\"may be extended\" due to poor weather forecast to lash the east coast.", "It has been 11 days since the search for William, who disappeared in 2014, was renewed in the wake of police receiving\u00a0new information.", "Hundreds of police officers and volunteers have braved wet weather over the past week, removing tonnes of soil and felling trees around Kendall.", "Police have also called in specialists such as archaeologists and hydrologists to help search for evidence in the dense bushland.", "Detective Chief Superintendent Darren Bennett said \"the weather has been atrocious\".", "\"It is obvious to all of us that we couldn't have picked a worse\u00a0time in terms of weather,\" he said.", "\"The update is the\u00a0search continues. It is painstaking.\u00a0It's difficult.", "\"We started\u00a0off with a time frame of between two\u00a0or three weeks. I\u00a0think we\u00a0have to double that now.\"", "", "
Police search\u00a0the home of William Tyrrell's foster-grandmother.(ABC News:\u00a0Emma Siossian)
", "Chief Superintendent Bennett said \"spirits are still high\" among\u00a0the investigators and search teams despite the frustration of constant stops and starts due to the weather.", "Numerous items have been found during\u00a0the search\u00a0and will be processed in Newcastle before being sent to Sydney for forensic DNA testing.", "\"The\u00a0message from the investigative team\u00a0is what they've located so far is\u00a0cause enough to keep going,\" he said.", "Three senior detectives were seen yesterday spending\u00a0hours sifting through soil removed from the ground by an excavator.", "Items found in the dirt were placed in two brown evidence bags. It's unclear what the items were, but they have been sent away for forensic analysis.", "Police divers have also been scouring a murky dam which runs between two farms in the Kendall area.\u00a0", "Officers are expected to return to bushland off Batar Creek Road\u00a0today."]
